{ Bringing the ballon closer to the cell

  Sometimes, the balloon is quite removed from the → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range/cell to which it is attached.

  In the → Microsoft/Office/Visual-Basic-Editor/Immediate-Window, after selecting the cell, the balloon can be brought closer to the cell by executing
code {
selection.comment.shape.left = selection.left : selection.comment.shape.top = selection.top + 50
code }

  Alternatively, a function can be created to bring mutliple comments nearer:
code {
sub bring_comments_near()
   for each c in selection
      if not c.comment is nothing then
         dim sh as shape
         set sh = c.comment.shape
         sh.left = c.left
         sh.top  = c.top + 50
       ' sh.textFrame.autoSize = true
      end if
   next c
end sub
code }

}

